article.headline: Youngstown St. 68, Cleveland St. 63
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Quin Humphrey had 22 points and 12 rebounds to lead Youngstown State to a 68-63 victory over Cleveland State on Saturday night, and the Penguins used a 6-2 run in the final 29 seconds to put the game away. Keston Roberts added 20 points for Youngstown State (9-11, 4-4 Horizon League), and John Barber had 18. J'Nathan Bullock led Cleveland State (7-14, 1-7) with 18 points. Raheem Moss had 14, Joe Davis 12 and Bahaadar Russell 11. Youngstown State led 33-28 at halftime. But Cleveland State started the second half with a 12-6 run, capped by a 3-pointer by Moss, to take a 40-39 lead with 12:38 to play. Barber made a pair of free throws to regain the lead for Youngstown State, and the Penguins never trailed again, even though Cleveland State pulled to within one at 62-61 on a 3-pointer by Moss with 40 seconds remaining. Down the stretch, Byron Davis and Humphrey each made a pair of free throws, and Barber's dunk with nine seconds left sealed the win.
